#. type: Title ==
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:16
msgid ""
"LINBIT(R) VSAN is a software-defined storage solution for hyperconverged "
"infrastructure, based on the LINBIT-developed link:https://github.com/LINBIT/"
"drbd[DRBD(R)] and link:https://github.com/LINBIT/linstor-server[LINSTOR(R)] "
"open source software.  It uses AlmaLinux 8 as a foundation and uses software "
"by LINBIT to offer highly available storage to hypervisors through a "
"convenient iSCSI target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:18
msgid ""
"It is built primarily with VMware ESXi as a target platform in mind, but it "
"is fully independent of the hypervisor software, so it should also work on "
"any other virtualization platform."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:21
msgid ""
"Not all best practices recommended in LINBIT how-to guides are implemented "
"yet.  For example, it is not yet possible to configure multiple links to "
"separate application and replication traffic."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Logically, LINBIT VSAN fits in between the hypervisor and the virtual "
"machines it offers storage for."
msgstr ""

#. type: Positional ($1) AttributeList argument for macro 'image'
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "images/vsan-architecture.svg"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:34
msgid ""
"In practice, VSAN runs one of its instances as a virtual machine on each "
"hypervisor in the cluster.  The hypervisor passes its local storage through "
"to VSAN, which then replicates the storage's data across the cluster.  One "
"of the VSAN virtual machines exports an iSCSI target through a static IP.  "
"This iSCSI target can be fed back to the hypervisor to offer a highly "
"available datastore.  The resulting datastore can be used to store virtual "
"machines and disk images on solid, redundant storage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:39
msgid "Before you can start using LINBIT VSAN, you need a few things first:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:42
msgid ""
"LINBIT customer credentials, which are also used to log in to the "
"link:https://my.linbit.com/[LINBIT Customer Portal].  You can get these by "
"link:https://www.linbit.com/request-linstor-vsan-download/[requesting an "
"evaluation]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:44
msgid ""
"A VSAN installation medium.  You will receive a download link upon "
"requesting an evaluation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:45
msgid "A virtualization platform, such as VMware ESXi."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:46
msgid ""
"Unrestricted internet access for all VSAN virtual machines.footnote:"
"[Internet access is only required during the initial setup, not for "
"continued operation.]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Number of nodes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:51
msgid ""
"Because VSAN makes use of the DRBD quorum mechanism, a VSAN cluster needs to "
"consist of at least three member nodes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:54
msgid ""
"The usual limitations and caveats of systems using quorum apply, for "
"example, an odd number of nodes is greatly preferred over an even one.  "
"Refer to the https://www.linbit.com/drbd-user-guide/drbd-guide-9_0-en/#s-"
"feature-quorum[\"Quorum\" section of the _DRBD 9 User Guide_] for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Operating system installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:59
msgid "LINBIT currently distributes VSAN in the following formats:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:61
msgid "As an *OVA image*, for environments based on a *VMware hypervisor*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:62
msgid "As an *ISO image*, for solutions powered by *any other hypervisor*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing by using OVA file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:67
msgid ""
"This is the easiest method, geared towards users of a *VMware hypervisor*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:69 UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:95
msgid "Take the following steps to set up your LINBIT VSAN cluster:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:71
msgid ""
"Import the OVA image into your VMware cluster. Make sure you create exactly "
"one VSAN virtual machine on each hypervisor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:72 UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:99
msgid ""
"Pass through the local storage devices that should be used by VSAN for data "
"replication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:74 UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:101
msgid ""
"Make sure the storage devices you pass through remain completely empty. For "
"example, do not create any partitions or LVM volumes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:75
msgid ""
"Start all VSAN virtual machines. Because the image already contains a ready-"
"made operating system, you are done. Next, start <<p-initialization,the VSAN "
"initialization process>> by navigating to the IP of one of your virtual "
"machines using your browser."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:78
msgid ""
"By default, the OVA image configures its network via DHCP.  If you need more "
"control (for example, a static IP or multiple addresses), you need to log in "
"to the VSAN virtual machine with the default credentials, and configure it "
"directly using the stock operating system tools."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:82
msgid ""
"When installing the operating system via the OVA image, a default password "
"is set so that the machine can be administered over SSH.  *The default "
"password for the `root` user is `linbit`*. Upon first login to a VSAN "
"virtual machine, the user is prompted to change the default password.  It is "
"*highly recommended* to log in to the machine over SSH and change the "
"password immediately after installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing by using ISO file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:88
msgid ""
"This method is appropriate as a fall-back option for all *non-VMware "
"hypervisors* that do not support importing OVA files.  Of course, it can "
"also be used on VMware hypervisors if you need more flexibility in the "
"operating system setup process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:93
msgid ""
"It is also possible to install LINBIT VSAN *directly to physical machines*, "
"eliminating the need for any hypervisor software to be present at all.  "
"Because LINBIT VSAN is based on the AlmaLinux operating system, their "
"guidelines for creating a physical installation medium apply.  For a guide "
"on how to write the LINBIT VSAN image to a physical medium, refer to the "
"link:https://wiki.almalinux.org/LiveMedia.html#how-to-download-and-write-"
"images[AlmaLinux Wiki page on the subject].  Simply use the LINBIT VSAN "
"appliance image in place of the AlmaLinux image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:97
msgid "Create one virtual machine for LINBIT VSAN on each hypervisor node."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:98
msgid "Attach one virtual or local disk for the operating system itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:102
msgid ""
"Assign at least one network adapter to each of the virtual machines. VSAN "
"acquires an IP address via DHCP."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:103
msgid ""
"Start the virtual machines and complete the operating system setup on each "
"machine. This is similar to a regular AlmaLinux 8 installation process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:106
msgid ""
"Do not use a Kickstart file to automate the installation process.  The VSAN "
"ISO already contains a Kickstart file to customize certain aspects of the "
"AlmaLinux 8 installer; providing an additional Kickstart file will cause "
"conflicts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:108
msgid ""
"Make sure you take note of the special requirements regarding <<s-iso-"
"networking,Networking>> and <<s-iso-time,Time>> during the setup process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:110
msgid ""
"You are done.  Next, start <<p-initialization,the VSAN initialization "
"process>> by navigating to the IP of one of your virtual machines using your "
"browser."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "Networking"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:116
msgid ""
"VSAN relies on a network connection being made available on boot.  By "
"default, the AlmaLinux installer configures the network interface to *not* "
"automatically connect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: UG9/en/vsan-user-guide.adoc:118
msgid ""
"When configuring the network interface, verify that the \"Connect "
"automatically with priority\" checkbox is checked."
msgstr ""

